# Fetch a plate from a carousel site to the Liconic transfer tray.
#
# Source resolution: if `plate_name` is non-empty the server looks it up
# in the registry and uses the recorded (cassette, position). Otherwise
# the explicit cassette/position fields must reference a registered
# plate. Positions are 1-indexed.
#
# The loading tray must be empty at the start of the call; on success
# the registry entry moves from the cassette site onto the tray and is
# persisted.
string plate_name                       # optional — registry lookup if non-empty
uint8 cassette                          # 1-indexed; required if plate_name is empty
uint8 position                          # 1-indexed; required if plate_name is empty
---
bool success
string message
string plate_name                       # echo of the plate fetched (for logging)
---
string stage                            # "validating" | "dispatching" | "waiting_ready" | "done"
